    <completion-summary>Completed 2026-06-03. Draft via sub-agent (commit cdaab907); Step 9.5 quality gates in main session. Output: docs/assessments/agent-framework-fit-assessment-2026-06-03.md (893 lines, target 800-1500). All 10 sections present and correctly numbered: §1 Executive summary (1-page, self-contained with 10-row recommendation table + 4 narrative paragraphs) · §2 Context+scope · §3 Current state inventory · §4 Feature map F1-F12 · §5 Per-surface matrix (10 surfaces + §5.11 summary table) · §6 Deployment recommendations · §7 Migration cost+risks (shared infra + publish-size + 10-row risk register + 8-17 PW estimate) · §8 Open questions (6 items, exceeds ≥3 floor) · §9 Forward-references (knowledge-r1 + ADR-013 + REFRESH cadence) · §10 Sources appendix (36 rows). Citations: 18 live primary URLs (13 Microsoft Learn + 3 Devblog + 2 GitHub Issue), 100% within 2026-04-01 recency floor (P12 one day below — inline stable-content justification per project rule). Closing line 893 enumerates 5 named owner decisions for action. Quality gates: adr-check ✅ no violations (2 forward-looking warnings on implied ADR-013 amendment for shared middleware lift + S5B prototyping recommendation — both correctly deferred to downstream PRs per scoping); code-review ✅ accepted with 2 warnings: (W1) S8a verdict changed from notes/04 PARTIAL to DON'T ADOPT based on deeper "textbook anti-fit" analysis — defensible but divergence not disclosed inline; (W2) two synthesis judgment-call extensions beyond notes/05 not flagged inline. Both warnings routed to task 007 adversarial review as inputs.</completion-summary>
