  <prompt>
    <goal>Write the canonical assessment document at docs/assessments/agent-framework-fit-assessment-YYYY-MM-DD.md by synthesizing notes/01 through notes/05. Required sections per SPEC §5: (1) Executive summary, (2) Context and scope, (3) Current state inventory, (4) Agent Framework feature map, (5) Per-surface decision matrix, (6) Deployment model recommendations, (7) Migration cost + risks, (8) Open questions / human-decision points, (9) Forward-references.</goal>
    <context>Tone reference: docs/assessments/bff-ai-extraction-assessment-2026-05-20.md. That assessment delivered "structurally AI-dominant but operationally justified" — honest, citation-backed, willing to acknowledge tension. This assessment must hit the same bar. The document is the project's primary output; all downstream decisions (ADR amendments, knowledge curation scope, future SPECs) reference this file.</context>
    <constraints>
      - File path: docs/assessments/agent-framework-fit-assessment-YYYY-MM-DD.md where YYYY-MM-DD is the synthesis date
      - All 9 sections from SPEC §5 — no skipping
      - Executive summary is FIRST and one page max — must stand alone if a reader reads only it
      - **Citation discipline (MANDATORY)**: every conclusion in §4 (feature map), §5 (recommendations), §6 (deployment), §7 (migration) cites at least ONE primary-source URL with fetched date (from notes/00-primary-source-baseline.md or task 003 captures). Spaarke-code claims cite file:line. ADR claims cite ADR number + section. NO recommendations citing only the curated knowledge/agent-framework/ snapshot — that snapshot is 3+ weeks stale by synthesis date
      - **Recency floor**: every primary-source citation MUST have a fetched-date no older than 60 days from synthesis date (i.e., if synthesis runs 2026-06-03, citations must be fetched 2026-04-03 or later). Older citations permitted ONLY for: foundational/conceptual pages that don't rev, ADRs, Spaarke internal docs. Any older citation must have a "stable content" justification inline
      - §8 open questions: 3+ items, each with "Why this is unresolved" + "What's needed to resolve"
      - §9 forward-references: explicit named projects/ADRs that this assessment unblocks or implies — including the parked agent-framework-knowledge-r1
      - **Add §10 Sources** appendix: complete table of every primary source cited in the document, with URL + fetched date + section(s) that reference it. Acts as the freshness audit trail
      - Tone: declarative ("S1 adopts Agent Framework's middleware composition pattern"). No hedging ("might want to consider"). When uncertain, say so explicitly in §8, not in the body
      - Length: 800-1500 lines target. BFF AI extraction assessment is in that range — match the depth
      - Do NOT edit ADR-013, do NOT edit agent-framework-knowledge-r1 SPEC — those are downstream (per scoping decision)
      - Length budget exception: if the surface count requires more, the assessment may run longer. Do not truncate analysis to fit a length cap
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
