  <steps>
    <step>Re-read docs/assessments/bff-ai-extraction-assessment-2026-05-20.md in full — internalize the tone, structure, citation style</step>
    <step>Re-read notes/01-05 in sequence — load all source findings into working context</step>
    <step>Draft §1 Executive summary — one page. Lead with the recommendation summary table from notes/04 closing; follow with 2-3 paragraphs naming the most consequential decisions and the most consequential open question</step>
    <step>Draft §2 Context and scope — surfaces evaluated (S1-S7 / S8 if found), what's out of scope (no code changes, no ADR amendments per scoping decision), the half-adopted starting state (Extensions.AI in prod, Agents.AI not yet)</step>
    <step>Draft §3 Current state inventory — synthesis of notes/01 + notes/02; structured table with surface | current state | abstractions used | deployment</step>
    <step>Draft §4 Agent Framework feature map — synthesis of notes/03; one row per feature category with what-it-is + Extensions.AI-baseline + Spaarke-applicability</step>
    <step>Draft §5 Per-surface decision matrix — synthesis of notes/04; one detailed subsection per surface with technical-fit + value + cost + recommendation + open question</step>
    <step>Draft §6 Deployment model recommendations — synthesis of notes/05; per surface, deployment model + cited ADR-013 criteria</step>
    <step>Draft §7 Migration cost + risks — synthesis of notes/05; total estimate, shared infra changes, risk register, publish-size analysis, reversibility</step>
    <step>Draft §8 Open questions / human-decision points — 3+ items; each with current-evidence + what's-needed-to-resolve</step>
    <step>Draft §9 Forward-references — projects this unblocks (agent-framework-knowledge-r1 SPEC refinement), ADRs this implies amendments to (ADR-013 §Constraints additions for Agent Framework adoption boundaries), future REFRESH cadence to re-check</step>
    <step>Draft §10 Sources appendix — table of every primary source cited: URL | fetched date | section(s) referencing | one-line content note. This is the freshness audit trail; readers + future REFRESH cycles use this to detect when conclusions need re-verification</step>
    <step>Recency audit (self-check before writing the file): scan §4-§7 citations. Confirm ≥80% are dated 2026-04-01 onwards. Any older citation must have a "stable content" justification inline. Flag any borderline items in §8 open questions</step>
    <step>Write to docs/assessments/agent-framework-fit-assessment-YYYY-MM-DD.md</step>
    <step>Run adr-check skill against the document (Step 9.5 of FULL rigor)</step>
    <step>Run code-review skill against the document as a deliverable (Step 9.5)</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(assessment): agent-framework fit assessment YYYY-MM-DD (R1 task 006)`</step>
  </steps>
